INEC in Taraba State will hire donkeys and canoes to distribute election materials in areas with difficult terrains for the 2019 general elections. The Head of Voters Education and Publicity in the commission, Mr. Fabian Vwamhi, disclosed this in an interview with our reporter in Jalingo. He said Sardauna, Gashaka, Karim-Lamido, Ibbi  and Yorro  local government areas had difficult terrains and therefore donkeys, motorcycles and canoes would be used to distribute election materials. Mr. Vwamhi further stated that 15,000 ad hoc staff were recruited by the commission for the 2019 general elections. He disclosed that those employed had commenced training in preparation for the conduct of the election. 2019: INEC to use donkeys, canoes during election in Taraba Ex-INEC boss, others blame INEC 2019: INEC urges religious leaders to preach against electoral violence